Package filemanager

Interface IStorageManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    StorageManager
    public interface IStorageManager
    This interface contains the abstraction of the methods that any class providing the logic to retrieve and store data should implement.

      • registerForCourse

        void registerForCourse​(java.lang.String userId,
                       java.lang.String courseCodeToBeAdded,
                       IndexNumber indexNumberToBeAdded)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        This method should contain the logic to register a student for a particular course and index number.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student to register the course and index number for.
        courseCodeToBeAdded - The course code of the course to register the student for.
        indexNumberToBeAdded - The IndexNumber object to register the student for.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there are clashes with any of the existing courses taken by the student, or if the student is already registered or in the wait list for the same course or if there is no vacancies for the particular index number, etc.

      • dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList

        void dropCourseAndRegisterNextStudentInWaitList​(java.lang.String userId,
                                                java.lang.String courseCodeToBeDropped,
                                                IndexNumber indexNumberToBeDropped)
                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        This method should contain the logic to drop a particular course and index number from the student and register the next student in the wait list for that index number.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student for which the course and index number will be dropped.
        courseCodeToBeDropped - The course code of the course which the student wants to drop.
        indexNumberToBeDropped - The IndexNumber object of the index number which the student wants to drop.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there are any issues with registering the next student in the wait list.

      • swapIndexNumber

        void swapIndexNumber​(java.lang.String userId,
                     java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped,
                     IndexNumber newIndexNumber)
              throws java.lang.Exception
        This method should provide the logic to swap index number for a particular course for a student.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student for which the index number will be swapped.
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The course code of the course for which the index number will swapped for the student.
        newIndexNumber - The IndexNumber object that represents the new index number that the student wants to swap to.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there are any issues with swapping the index number, e.g. no vacancies for the new index number, clashes with any of the existing courses, etc.

      • swapIndexWithPeer

        void swapIndexWithPeer​(java.lang.String userId,
                       java.lang.String peerUserId,
                       java.lang.String courseCodeToBeSwapped)
                throws java.lang.Exception
        This method should contain the logic to swap an index number with another peer.
        Parameters:
        userId - The user id of the student initiating the swap.
        peerUserId - The user id of the peer that is swapping with the student.
        courseCodeToBeSwapped - The course code of the course that is to be swapped by the student and the peer.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if there is any issues with the swap, e.g. clashes with any of the existing courses taken by the student or the peer.

                      int index,
                      int newMaxVacancy)
               throws java.lang.Exception
        This method should contain the logic for setting the new max vacancy for an existing index number.
        Parameters:
        courseCode - The course code of the course for which the existing index number is associated with.
        index - The index of the index numbers that are associated with the course.
        newMaxVacancy - The new maximum vacancy of the existing index number.
        Throws:
